We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.

Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

BEST OF EST | Heritage Revivals in Melbourne’s Fitzroy
​.
​​We head to Melbourne’s Fitzroy to spotlight five heritage homes brought into the modern-day through sensitive architectural intervention.
​.
​Inside this feature you'll find this tactful revival of an early Victorian Fitzroy terrace by @robkennonarchitects.
​.
@robkennonarchitects have retained key aspects of the heritage home throughout, subtly gesturing to its 150-year-old bones through exposed original internal bluestone walls, aged Baltic Pine flooring and traditional Roman archway. 
​.
​See all four homes inside this 'Best of est' feature via the link in profile. 
​.
​Design @robkennonarchitects
​Photography @derekswalwell 
​.

DESIGNER FOCUS | Happy Birthday Pierre Yovanovitch!
​
In the spirit of French interior architect @pierre.yovanovitch's birthday, we're revisiting his own home which he shared with us in est Magazine Issue #37  - Chateau Fabregues, set in the lavender foothills of the high alps in Provence, France.
